headline: GE Vernova stock drops around AI concerns, P&G upgraded to Buy
summary: Market Domination host Josh Lipton and Yahoo Finance senior reporter Brooke DiPalma track several of the day's top trending stock tickers, including GE Vernova (GEV) stock dropping amid investor concerns around the future of AI data centers, Jefferies analysts upgrading shares of Procter & Gamble (PG) to a Buy rating, and Gap, Inc. (GAP) receiving two upgrades to Outperform. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination.

headline: Medline makes Nasdaq debut, Procter & Gamble upgraded to Buy
summary: Yahoo Finance anchor Josh Lipton tracks Wednesday's top moving stocks and biggest market stories in this Market Minute. Medical supply company Medline (MDLN) made its debut on the Nasdaq Composite (^IXIC) at $35 per share, the biggest public offering of 2025. Procter & Gamble (PG) was upgraded to Buy from Hold by Jefferies. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.
